00:03:09.460 --> 00:03:14.500
what we try to bring to life
in this book, "Drawdown".

00:03:14.500 --> 00:03:18.610
Drawdown is the product of a
nonprofit living, research,

00:03:18.610 --> 00:03:21.400
and communications project
on climate solutions

00:03:21.400 --> 00:03:23.170
called Project Drawdown,
which is actually

00:03:23.170 --> 00:03:26.140
just based in Sausalito.

00:03:26.140 --> 00:03:27.760
If you think about
global warming

00:03:27.760 --> 00:03:32.890
as kind of the ultimate problem
statement, for many years

00:03:32.890 --> 00:03:35.260
our founder and
executive director

00:03:35.260 --> 00:03:38.710
and editor of the book,
Paul Hawken, really wrestled

00:03:38.710 --> 00:03:41.230
with a set of
persistent questions

00:03:41.230 --> 00:03:44.620
in the face of problem, problem,
problem, problem, which was,

00:03:44.620 --> 00:03:47.290
do we actually know what
we're supposed to be doing?

00:03:47.290 --> 00:03:48.910
Do we have a list?

00:03:48.910 --> 00:03:52.420
Do we have a sense of
apples to apples comparison

00:03:52.420 --> 00:03:56.140
of existing solutions,
technologies, and practices

00:03:56.140 --> 00:03:59.860
that we already know work,
that are already proven?

00:03:59.860 --> 00:04:02.920
And then how much could
they each contribute?

00:04:02.920 --> 00:04:05.890
If we scaled them
vigorously but plausibly

00:04:05.890 --> 00:04:08.830
between now and
mid-century, let's say,

00:04:08.830 --> 00:04:11.340
how much of the needle
can they each move

00:04:11.340 --> 00:04:14.150
when it comes to
addressing global warming?

00:04:14.150 --> 00:04:18.000
So Paul being Paul, he
sort of pitched this notion

00:04:18.000 --> 00:04:21.220
to lots of different
organizations and folks,

00:04:21.220 --> 00:04:23.000
all of whom said, a
list would be great.

00:04:23.000 --> 00:04:25.720
We're not in the
business of doing that.

00:04:25.720 --> 00:04:29.290
And eventually Project Drawdown
was born to do the math

00:04:29.290 --> 00:04:31.990
and answer these
questions, and then

00:04:31.990 --> 00:04:34.660
ultimately to bring
the answers to life,

00:04:34.660 --> 00:04:40.150
not in yet another dry and
impenetrable and wonky climate

00:04:40.150 --> 00:04:41.920
report, but in a
way that we hope

00:04:41.920 --> 00:04:45.460
is really accessible and
instructive and maybe

00:04:45.460 --> 00:04:48.610
even inspiring for
anyone, and not

00:04:48.610 --> 00:04:52.240
just for folks who think
of themselves as experts

00:04:52.240 --> 00:04:54.140
on climate.

