00:51:14.530 --> 00:51:17.880
which is how do
we actually engage

00:51:17.880 --> 00:51:21.570
in this process of
pulling carbon back down

00:51:21.570 --> 00:51:22.620
out of the atmosphere?

00:51:22.620 --> 00:51:24.840
How do we do drawdown
as a company, where

00:51:24.840 --> 00:51:27.900
we're pulling more
greenhouse gases down

00:51:27.900 --> 00:51:30.450
than we're sending up?

00:51:30.450 --> 00:51:33.160
Again, it's a big
and bold mission,

00:51:33.160 --> 00:51:35.880
and they don't know how
they will get there.

00:51:35.880 --> 00:51:38.730
Sequestering carbon in their
products is probably something.

00:51:38.730 --> 00:51:41.670
They're already working
with Janine Benyus

00:51:41.670 --> 00:51:44.880
and brilliant biomimicry
team around how do you

00:51:44.880 --> 00:51:48.730
design a factory like a forest
so that it actually exhales

00:51:48.730 --> 00:51:50.220
net good into the world?

00:51:50.220 --> 00:51:53.490
I think these are the kinds
of really big questions

00:51:53.490 --> 00:51:54.690
we should ask.

00:51:54.690 --> 00:51:56.910
Lots of companies now
are doing good stuff

00:51:56.910 --> 00:51:59.400
